# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backstory Automation Library — environment variables
#
# These are the credentials to add in Vercel:
#   Project → Settings → Environment Variables  (set for "Production")
# After adding/changing them, redeploy for the change to take effect.
# Copy this file to `.env` for a local `vercel dev` run (it is gitignored).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── REQUIRED: the AI assistant ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Server-side Anthropic API key. Without it, the "Ask AI" popup still appears
# but every reply is the "assistant is offline" message.
# Get one at: https://console.anthropic.com  →  API Keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-replace-me

# Optional: which Claude model the assistant uses.
# Default is claude-opus-4-8. Set claude-sonnet-4-6 for cheaper / faster chat.
ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# ── OPTIONAL: "Submit to marketplace" (files a GitHub issue) ──────────────────
# Without GITHUB_TOKEN, submissions fall back to a prefilled "new issue" link.
# Token: github.com → Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens.
#   - Classic: scope `repo`  (or fine-grained: Issues = Read/Write on the repo)
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_replace-me

# owner/repo that submissions are filed into. Use the repo's CURRENT location.
GITHUB_REPO=jamesmcdaniel-cyber/Backstory_Workflows
